# Route Pattern

## Goal

Establish consistent RESTful route structure for all resource endpoints.

## Convention

| Rule | Implementation |
|------|----------------|
| Resource routers are mounted at `/<resource>` | `app.use('/users', usersRouter)` |
| List endpoint at `GET /` | Returns array of all resources |
| Single resource at `GET /:id` | Returns one resource by ID |
| Create at `POST /` | Creates new resource, returns 201 |
| ID parsing uses `parseInt` | `parseInt(req.params.id)` |

## Applies To

| Component | Routes |
|-----------|--------|
| c3-103 Users Router | `/users`, `/users/:id` |
| c3-104 Products Router | `/products`, `/products/:id` |

## Pattern Template

```typescript
import { Router } from 'express';

export const resourceRouter = Router();

// List all
resourceRouter.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.json(resources);
});

// Get by ID
resourceRouter.get('/:id', (req, res) => {
  const resource = resources.find(r => r.id === parseInt(req.params.id));
  if (!resource) {
    return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Resource not found' });
  }
  res.json(resource);
});

// Create
resourceRouter.post('/', (req, res) => {
  const newResource = { id: resources.length + 1, ...req.body };
  resources.push(newResource);
  res.status(201).json(newResource);
});
```

## Source Files

- `src/routes/users.ts`
- `src/routes/products.ts`

